               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370102-name-232" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-232" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-232" type="surname" value="WREN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-232" type="given" value="ERASMUS"></interp>ERASMUS WREN</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Fenchurch-street. About half-past ten o'clock, on the evening of the 18th of December, I was on Holborn-bridge</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183701020036"></xptr>
               <p>—I felt a person taking my handkerchief, I turned round and secured the prisoner, who was the only person near me—he had not my handker<lb></lb>chief in his possession, but it was dropped behind him—there was no else within ten yards of me—I charged him with taking it—he denied it and struggled very much to get away; and the other person, whom I saw about ten yards off, rushed upon me and struck me, and ran off imme<lb></lb>diately.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I showed him the man that picked his pocket. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. He did after he had ran off, but it could not possibly have been that other man, he was so far off.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370102-name-233" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-233" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-233" type="surname" value="WILLIAMS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-233" type="given" value="EBENEZER"></interp>EBENEZER WILLIAMS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an officer. I took the prisoner at the watch-house—the prosecutor's nose was bleeding when he came then, through the blow he had had, and the handkerchief was all bloody.</p>
               <p>
